 Corporate Briefs
																								 Balmer Lawrie clocked a profit after tax of Rs 68.79 crore in the half year ended September 30 against Rs 55.36 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. Net profit for the quarter ended September 30 was Rs 25.99 crore compared with Rs 18.95 crore a year ago. Total income for the quarter rose to Rs 363.48 crore from Rs 321.85 crore. Total income for the half year stood at Rs 726.15 crore against Rs 635.33 crore.																								 Container Corporation Ltd (Concor) has clocked a net profit of Rs 174.2 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal against Rs 189.5 crore in the same quarter of the previous fiscal. Operating profit was Rs 212.3 crore in the quarter compared with Rs 252.2 crore a year ago. The companys net sales stood at Rs 818.8 crore against Rs 769.3 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.																								 Gontermann-Peipers (India) Ltd has reported a net profit of Rs 2.96 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 against Rs 3.63 crore a year ago. The companys net turnover rose to Rs 41.89 crore in the quarter from Rs 39.29 crore a year ago. ADVERTISEMENT
